<subSubSection id="2E7F8F32985C2E70F30AF53E5EDC5B3A" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D38C883F40D57F3B21BA587F0C03B87" box="[19,927,2015,2339]" pageId="25" pageNumber="278" type="mainText">Annual herbs with at least some inconspicuous T-shaped hairs. Leaves alternate or opposite, narrow. Flowers bisexual, solitary, subtended by 2 navicular bracteoles; perianth lobes 2-5, unmodified in fruit; stamens 1-5; disk inconspicuous; stigmas 2, filiform. Pericarp scarious, smooth; seed vertical. ll spp., SE Europe, W and C Asia.</paragraph>
